---
// Utils
import { getImage } from "astro:assets";

// Components
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import AboutHero from "@/components/About/AboutHero.astro";
import AboutStory from "@/components/About/AboutStory.astro";
import AboutCredentials from "@/components/About/AboutCredentials.astro";
import AboutHowWeWork from "@/components/About/AboutHowWeWork.astro";

// Images
import landingImage from "@/assets/images/landing.jpg";
const optimizedImage = await getImage({ src: landingImage, format: "webp" });
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about Rod's Electrical, a locally owned Edmonton electrical company with 14+ years of residential and commercial experience."
  heroImage={optimizedImage}
>
  {
    /*
    ABOUT PAGE MASTER PLAN

    Purpose:
    - Port and redesign https://rodselectrical.ca/about-us/ into Astro.
    - Build section by section without losing page structure or repeating strategy work.
    - Future LLMs should treat this comment as source-of-truth for layout order, section scope, and content direction.

    Primary page goal:
    - Establish trust fast.
    - Tell company story clearly.
    - Prove qualifications and work standards.
    - End with one strong quote/contact CTA.

    Final section order:
    1. Hero
    2. Story
    3. Credentials
    4. How We Work
    5. Who We Help
    6. CTA

    IMPORTANT WORKFLOW RULES FOR FUTURE EDITS
    - If user asks for one section only, implement only that section and keep rest unchanged.
    - Do not redesign whole page unless user explicitly asks for full-page pass.
    - Preserve final section order above even if only one section is being built now.
    - Avoid repeating same trust message in multiple sections.
    - Do not clone contact page into this page. CTA should be lighter than full contact page unless user says otherwise.
    - Prefer real company/founder/jobsite imagery over generic stock if assets become available.
    - Keep copy grounded in existing site content. Tighten language, but do not invent unsupported claims.

    CONTENT SOURCE FROM CURRENT WORDPRESS ABOUT PAGE
    Source URL: https://rodselectrical.ca/about-us/
    Reusable facts already stated on live site:
    - Locally owned and operated company.
    - Over 14 years of industry / hands-on field experience.
    - Serves homeowners and businesses.
    - Focus on safety, trust, craftsmanship, integrity, code compliance, and quality work that lasts.
    - Goal is to do job right first time and treat every property like it is their own.
    - Qualifications listed: Journeyman Certified Electrician, Project Management Certified, CSTS Certified,
      WHMIS Certified, Fall Protection Trained, Professional Estimation Expertise, Fully Licensed & Insured.
    - Service approach listed: honest pricing, clear communication, on-time completion, clean organized worksites,
      safe compliant installations, long-term customer relationships.

    CONTENT HYGIENE
    - "Mission", "Vision", "Core Values", "Why Choose Us", and "Our Approach" overlap heavily on live page.
    - In this Astro version, merge overlapping ideas into clearer sections instead of repeating them.
    - Avoid filler headings like "What We Do" if section is actually values or company philosophy.

    SECTION-BY-SECTION SPEC

    SECTION 1: HERO
    Goal:
    - Immediate trust and positioning.
    Must communicate:
    - Local Edmonton electrical company.
    - 14+ years experience.
    - Licensed / insured / certified.
    - Residential and commercial support.
    Suggested content shape:
    - Eyebrow: "About Rods Electrical" or similar.
    - H1 focused on trust, not generic "About Us".
    - One short supporting paragraph.
    - 3 to 4 proof chips or stat pills.
    - Primary CTA to quote/contact, secondary CTA to call.
    - One strong image only.
    Do not:
    - Dump full story paragraph here.
    - Repeat every certification here.

    SECTION 2: STORY
    Goal:
    - Explain who company is, what they believe, and how they work.
    Source content to reshape:
    - Great electrical work is not just wires and panels; it is about safety, trust, and lasting quality.
    - Locally owned and operated.
    - Proudly served homeowners and businesses.
    - Focus from day one: do job right first time, follow code, treat every property like their own.
    Suggested content shape:
    - 2-column layout works well.
    - One main narrative block.
    - Optional side callouts for "Locally owned", "Code-first", "Respectful workmanship".
    Do not:
    - Turn this into generic mission/vision cards.
    - Repeat detailed certification checklist here.

    SECTION 3: CREDENTIALS
    Goal:
    - Hard proof of competence and safety.
    Source items:
    - 14+ years hands-on field experience.
    - Journeyman Certified Electrician.
    - Project Management Certified.
    - CSTS Certified.
    - WHMIS Certified.
    - Fall Protection Trained.
    - Professional Estimation Expertise.
    - Fully Licensed & Insured Company.
    Suggested content shape:
    - Badge grid, checklist, or certification cards.
    - Could include short intro sentence explaining client is hiring trained, certified, experienced professionals.
    Do not:
    - Mix this with soft brand values.

    SECTION 4: HOW WE WORK
    Goal:
    - Show practical service standards and client experience.
    Merge these live-page ideas:
    - Honest and transparent pricing.
    - Clear communication from start to finish.
    - On-time project completion.
    - Clean, organized worksites.
    - Safe and compliant installations.
    - Long-term relationships with customers.
    Suggested content shape:
    - 4 to 6 principle cards or checklist with short descriptions.
    - This section replaces separate "Why Choose Us" and "Our Approach" duplication.
    Do not:
    - Reuse same exact bullets from hero proof chips.

    SECTION 5: WHO WE HELP
    Goal:
    - Bridge About page into service intent.
    Must communicate:
    - Homeowners.
    - Businesses.
    - Repairs, upgrades, installations, ongoing electrical needs.
    Suggested content shape:
    - 2 to 3 cards max.
    - Each card can link to service pages if useful.
    Do not:
    - Turn this into full services index.

    SECTION 6: CTA
    Goal:
    - Give clear next step after trust is established.
    Suggested content shape:
    - Short quote/contact block.
    - Strong CTA button plus phone number.
    - Optional promise like response time if already used elsewhere in brand.
    Do not:
    - Duplicate full contact page form unless user explicitly wants it here.

    IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
    - Build with semantic sections and stable IDs so later edits are easy.
    - Good IDs:
      - about-hero
      - about-story
      - about-credentials
      - about-process
      - about-audience
      - about-cta
    - Prefer reusable components if repo already has suitable patterns; otherwise build page-specific sections cleanly.
    - Keep mobile layout first-class. No desktop-only composition.
    - Tone should feel professional, trustworthy, and local; not corporate-heavy.
  */
  }

  {
    /*
    SECTION PLACEHOLDERS
    Keep order below. Implement progressively.

    <section id="about-hero">...</section>
    <section id="about-story">...</section>
    <section id="about-credentials">...</section>
    <section id="about-process">...</section>
    <section id="about-audience">...</section>
    <section id="about-cta">...</section>
  */
  }

  <AboutHero image={optimizedImage} />
  <AboutStory variant="editorial" />
  <AboutCredentials />
  <AboutHowWeWork />
</BaseLayout>
